  "body": "Captured from https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/27914#issuecomment-228140108\n\nToday the SetUpPod() is called before the rkt pod is actually running (which enables we have the pod IP before hand and inject that into Downward API and /etc/hosts). \n\nHowever in the SetUpPod(), it will list try to maintain the host port iptable rules by gathering all the host ports from running pods, which will cause a race when multiple pods starts at the same time as described in the above linked comment.\n\ncc @kubernetes/sig-rktnetes @kubernetes/sig-node @kubernetes/sig-network \n",
